<% content_for :title, "BioVeL Portal - About Cookies"%>
<div style="float:left;width:65%">
  <h1>About Cookies:</h1>
  </br>
  <p>
    Article 5(3) of the EU e-Privacy Directive requires to inform users about 
    the use of cookies, the purpose that the cookie will be used for and the 
    right to opt-out of the use of cookies. 
  </p>
  <p>
    BioVeL Portal uses Google Analytics to monitor usage - This information is 
    used to help deliver the service, and to monitor capacity and use only. 
    Currently there is not mechanism for individuals to opt out of this 
    monitoring. Your only option would be not to use the portal. 
  </p>
  <p> 
    BioVeL Portal will set a session cookie. This cookie is used to validate 
    information sent to process user actions, for guest and registered users 
    alike. 
    BioVeL Portal will also set an authentication cookie for logged in users. 
    This is used to carry the “logged in” status from one page to the next, 
    which is essential to the function of the site and not used for any other 
    purpose.
  </p>
  <p> 
    Please contact us for further information and to express your views on this
    policy.
  </p>
  <p> 
    You can email comments and suggestions to : support@biovel.eu 
  </p>
  <p>
    BioVeL 
  </p>
</div>
